{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775876638775,"sessionID":"ses_28582da2affeRZIOU7psqXd8oK","part":{"id":"prt_d7a7f07d90012TTreiY5oQvWD5","messageID":"msg_d7a7de92f001HGfc2A6IHWBMwZ","sessionID":"ses_28582da2affeRZIOU7psqXd8oK","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-40f3e72a0a0c4526ae10a2187328c6cd","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","content":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-025 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n\n1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)\n4. **CLI Option Mapping**: Map Typer CLI options to metadata updates via `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n\n**Current State**: No dedicated metadata service or data models exist. CLI commands directly handle YAML files without schema validation, leading to inconsistent metadata handling and potential configuration errors.\n\n**Target State**: \n- `MetadataService` class with load/save/update/validate methods\n- `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with 20+ fields and validators\n- `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI-to-metadata option mapping\n- Consistent error handling for invalid metadata files\n- Unit test coverage for validation scenarios\n\n---\n\n## 2. Scope (范围)\n\n### 2.1 In Scope\n\n| Deliverable | Description |\n|-------------|-------------|\n| `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class for metadata lifecycle management |\n| `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI options |\n| `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n| `tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Unit tests for MetadataService |\n| `tests/test_agent_metadata.py` | Unit tests for AgentMetadata validators |\n\n### 2.2 MetadataService Methods\n\n| Method | Purpose |\n|--------|---------|\n| `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose logging flag |\n| `load_metadata(workspace_path)` | Load `AgentMetadata` from YAML with fallback filenames |\n| `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` | Persist metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n| `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` | Apply partial updates and return new metadata |\n| `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` | Validate workspace directory and file structure |\n| `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for *.py files in Python workspace |\n| `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for pom.xml in Java workspace |\n\n### 2.3 AgentMetadata Model Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Default | Validation |\n|-------|------|---------|------------|\n| `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Unique agent identifier |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n| `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Validator: `['python', 'java']` lowercase |\n| `entrypoint` | `str` | Required | Command to launch agent |\n| `port` | `int` | `8080` | Validator: `1..65535` |\n| `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Validator: `['local', 'cloud']` lowercase |\n| `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n| `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version for publishing |\n| `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image info |\n| `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication config |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for publishing |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Readiness probe path |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Readiness probe port |\n| `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n| `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session ID for agent |\n| `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment info |\n\n### 2.4 MetadataOptions Fields\n\n| Field | Type | Default |\n|-------|------|---------|\n| `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n| `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n| `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n| `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n| `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n| `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n\n### 2.5 Out of Scope\n\n| Item | Reason |\n|------|--------|\n| Database-backed metadata storage | YAML file storage per spec; database would be separate feature |\n| Metadata encryption/secrets | Security handled by separate secret management (future) |\n| Multi-agent metadata aggregation | Single agent per workspace per spec |\n| Version history tracking | Git handles versioning; metadata file is single state |\n| Cloud metadata sync | Metadata is local file; cloud sync would be separate feature |\n\n---\n\n## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n\n### 3.1 新增文件\n\n```\ncmd/cli/\n├── agentcube/\n│   ├── models/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py           # NEW: models package marker\n│   │   └── pack_models.py        # NEW: MetadataOptions dataclass\n│   ├── services/\n│   │   ├── __init__.py           # MODIFY: export MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n│   │   └── metadata_service.py   # NEW: MetadataService class\n│   └── runtime/\n│   │   └── pack_runtime.py       # MODIFY: use MetadataService\n│   └── cli/\n│       └── main.py               # MODIFY: use MetadataOptions for pack command\n└── tests/\n    ├── test_metadata_service.py  # NEW: MetadataService unit tests\n    └── test_agent_metadata.py    # NEW: AgentMetadata validator tests\n```\n\n### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n\n| Dependency | Version | Impact |\n|------------|---------|--------|\n| `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | BaseModel for AgentMetadata; validators for field constraints |\n| `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for metadata file persistence |\n| `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling for workspace validation |\n| Standard library `logging` | stdlib | Verbose logging support |\n\n### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n\n| Consumer | Method Usage |\n|----------|--------------|\n| `PackRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()` |\n| `BuildRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for version increment |\n| `PublishRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for deployment info |\n| `InvokeRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for endpoint retrieval |\n| `StatusRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for status display |\n| CLI `pack` command | `MetadataOptions.from_options()` for CLI option mapping |\n\n### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n\n- **Metadata file name**: Primary filename is `agent_metadata.yaml`; fallbacks are `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n- **Schema validation**: Existing metadata files must conform to new validators; invalid language/build_mode will raise errors\n- **Required fields**: `agent_name` and `entrypoint` are now required; existing files missing these will fail validation\n- **Port validation**: Port must be 1-65535; values outside range will be rejected\n\n---\n\n## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n\n### Alternative 1: dataclasses instead of Pydantic\n\n**Approach**: Use Python `dataclasses` for `AgentMetadata` with manual validation methods.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | No external dependency; simpler for basic data structures |\n| Cons | No automatic validation; more boilerplate; no serialization helpers; no type coercion |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Pydantic provides automatic validation, type coercion, and `model_dump()` for serialization without boilerplate.\n\n### Alternative 2: JSON-based metadata storage\n\n**Approach**: Store metadata as JSON instead of YAML.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Native Python `json` module; no pyyaml dependency; easier machine parsing |\n| Cons | Less human-readable; no comments support; spec explicitly requires YAML |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires YAML format (`agent_metadata.yaml`) for human-readable configuration with comments.\n\n### Alternative 3: Single metadata file in home directory\n\n**Approach**: Store all agent metadata in a central file (e.g., `~/.agentcube/metadata.yaml`) instead of workspace-local files.\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Centralized management; easier multi-agent overview |\n| Cons | Workspace independence lost; harder to version control; spec requires per-workspace file |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` for workspace-local configuration and Git version control.\n\n### Alternative 4: Configuration file inheritance/templating\n\n**Approach**: Support base metadata file with inheritance (e.g., `extends: base-metadata.yaml`).\n\n| Aspect | Evaluation |\n|--------|------------|\n| Pros | Reuse common settings; reduce duplication |\n| Cons | Adds complexity; not in spec; inheritance resolution overhead |\n\n**Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as enhancement if users request configuration reuse patterns.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Risks\n\n| Risk | Mitigation |\n|------|------------|\n| Invalid YAML syntax | `yaml.safe_load` raises `YAMLDecodeError`; catch and re-raise with context |\n| Missing required fields | Pydantic `ValidationError` with field-specific messages |\n| Unknown fields in YAML | Pydantic `extra=\"ignore\"` (or forbid per spec requirement) |\n| Workspace validation race condition | Check file existence before validation; handle `FileNotFoundError` |\n| Language mismatch | `_validate_python_workspace` / `_validate_java_workspace` with clear error messages |\n| Port range violation | Pydantic validator `validate_port` raises `ValueError` with valid range |\n\n---\n\n## 6. Implementation Checklist\n\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/models/__init__.py` package marker\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options(options: Dict[str, Any])` factory method\n- [ ] Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` with fallback filenames\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` with YAML options\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` partial update\n- [ ] Implement `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` structure check\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_python_workspace` for *.py file check\n- [ ] Implement `_validate_java_workspace` for pom.xml check\n- [ ] Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all fields\n- [ ] Implement `validate_language` validator (python/java lowercase)\n- [ ] Implement `validate_build_mode` validator (local/cloud lowercase)\n- [ ] Implement `validate_port` validator (1-65535 range)\n- [ ] Update `agentcube/services/__init__.py` exports\n- [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n- [ ] Add unit tests for metadata load/save with valid YAML\n- [ ] Add unit tests for fallback filename behavior\n- [ ] Add unit tests for Pydantic validators\n- [ ] Add unit tests for workspace validation scenarios\n- [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py` to validate\n\n---\n\n## 7. References\n\n- Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Metadata file format, Workspace validation\n- Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — MetadataService, AgentMetadata, MetadataOptions signatures\n- AR-021 — CLI pack command (uses MetadataService for pack flow)\n- AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses metadata for deployment info)\n- Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n- PyYAML Documentation: https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876638754,"end":1775876638773}}}}
