alidators\n28: - `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI-to-metadata option mapping\n29: - Consistent error handling for invalid metadata files\n30: - Unit test coverage for validation scenarios\n31: \n32: ---\n33: \n34: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n35: \n36: ### 2.1 In Scope\n37: \n38: | Deliverable | Description |\n39: |-------------|-------------|\n40: | `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` | `MetadataService` class for metadata lifecycle management |\n41: | `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` | `MetadataOptions` dataclass for CLI options |\n42: | `agentcube/services/__init__.py` | Services package exports |\n43: | `tests/test_metadata_service.py` | Unit tests for MetadataService |\n44: | `tests/test_agent_metadata.py` | Unit tests for AgentMetadata validators |\n45: \n46: ### 2.2 MetadataService Methods\n47: \n48: | Method | Purpose |\n49: |--------|---------|\n50: | `__init__(verbose)` | Initialize service with verbose logging flag |\n51: | `load_metadata(workspace_path)` | Load `AgentMetadata` from YAML with fallback filenames |\n52: | `save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` | Persist metadata to `agent_metadata.yaml` |\n53: | `update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` | Apply partial updates and return new metadata |\n54: | `validate_workspace(workspace_path)` | Validate workspace directory and file structure |\n55: | `_validate_python_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for *.py files in Python workspace |\n56: | `_validate_java_workspace(workspace_path, metadata)` | Check for pom.xml in Java workspace |\n57: \n58: ### 2.3 AgentMetadata Model Fields\n59: \n60: | Field | Type | Default | Validation |\n61: |-------|------|---------|------------|\n62: | `agent_name` | `str` | Required | Unique agent identifier |\n63: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Human-readable summary |\n64: | `language` | `str` | `\"python\"` | Validator: `['python', 'java']` lowercase |\n65: | `entrypoint` | `str` | Required | Command to launch agent |\n66: | `port` | `int` | `8080` | Validator: `1..65535` |\n67: | `build_mode` | `str` | `\"local\"` | Validator: `['local', 'cloud']` lowercase |\n68: | `region` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Deployment region |\n69: | `version` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Semantic version for publishing |\n70: | `image` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Container image info |\n71: | `auth` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Authentication config |\n72: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `\"requirements.txt\"` | Python dependency file |\n73: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry URL for publishing |\n74: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry username |\n75: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` | Registry password |\n76: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent endpoint URL |\n77: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Workload Manager URL |\n78: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Router URL |\n79: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Readiness probe path |\n80: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `None` | Readiness probe port |\n81: | `agent_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Agent ID assigned by AgentCube |\n82: | `session_id` | `Optional[str]` | `None` | Session ID for agent |\n83: | `k8s_deployment` | `Optional[Dict[str, Any]]` | `None` | Kubernetes deployment info |\n84: \n85: ### 2.4 MetadataOptions Fields\n86: \n87: | Field | Type | Default |\n88: |-------|------|---------|\n89: | `agent_name` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n90: | `language` | `Optional[str]` | `'python'` |\n91: | `entrypoint` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n92: | `port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n93: | `build_mode` | `Optional[str]` | `'local'` |\n94: | `requirements_file` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n95: | `description` | `Optional[str]` | `None` |\n96: | `workload_manager_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n97: | `router_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n98: | `readiness_probe_path` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n99: | `readiness_probe_port` | `Optional[int]` | `8080` |\n100: | `registry_url` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n101: | `registry_username` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n102: | `registry_password` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n103: | `agent_endpoint` | `Optional[str]` | `\"\"` |\n104: \n105: ### 2.5 Out of Scope\n106: \n107: | Item | Reason |\n108: |------|--------|\n109: | Database-backed metadata storage | YAML file storage per spec; database would be separate feature |\n110: | Metadata encryption/secrets | Security handled by separate secret management (future) |\n111: | Multi-agent metadata aggregation | Single agent per workspace per spec |\n112: | Version history tracking | Git handles versioning; metadata file is single state |\n113: | Cloud metadata sync | Metadata is local file; cloud sync would be separate feature |\n114: \n115: ---\n116: \n117: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n118: \n119: ### 3.1 新增文件\n120: \n121: ```\n122: cmd/cli/\n123: ├── agentcube/\n124: │   ├── models/\n125: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # NEW: models package marker\n126: │   │   └── pack_models.py        # NEW: MetadataOptions dataclass\n127: │   ├── services/\n128: │   │   ├── __init__.py           # MODIFY: export MetadataService, AgentMetadata\n129: │   │   └── metadata_service.py   # NEW: MetadataService class\n130: │   └── runtime/\n131: │   │   └── pack_runtime.py       # MODIFY: use MetadataService\n132: │   └── cli/\n133: │       └── main.py               # MODIFY: use MetadataOptions for pack command\n134: └── tests/\n135:     ├── test_metadata_service.py  # NEW: MetadataService unit tests\n136:     └── test_agent_metadata.py    # NEW: AgentMetadata validator tests\n137: ```\n138: \n139: ### 3.2 Upstream Dependencies\n140: \n141: | Dependency | Version | Impact |\n142: |------------|---------|--------|\n143: | `pydantic` | `>=2.0.0` | BaseModel for AgentMetadata; validators for field constraints |\n144: | `pyyaml` | `>=6.0` | YAML load/dump for metadata file persistence |\n145: | `pathlib` | stdlib | Path handling for workspace validation |\n146: | Standard library `logging` | stdlib | Verbose logging support |\n147: \n148: ### 3.3 Downstream Consumers\n149: \n150: | Consumer | Method Usage |\n151: |----------|--------------|\n152: | `PackRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `save_metadata()`, `validate_workspace()` |\n153: | `BuildRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for version increment |\n154: | `PublishRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()`, `update_metadata()` for deployment info |\n155: | `InvokeRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for endpoint retrieval |\n156: | `StatusRuntime` | `MetadataService.load_metadata()` for status display |\n157: | CLI `pack` command | `MetadataOptions.from_options()` for CLI option mapping |\n158: \n159: ### 3.4 Breaking Change Considerations\n160: \n161: - **Metadata file name**: Primary filename is `agent_metadata.yaml`; fallbacks are `agent.yaml`, `metadata.yaml`\n162: - **Schema validation**: Existing metadata files must conform to new validators; invalid language/build_mode will raise errors\n163: - **Required fields**: `agent_name` and `entrypoint` are now required; existing files missing these will fail validation\n164: - **Port validation**: Port must be 1-65535; values outside range will be rejected\n165: \n166: ---\n167: \n168: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n169: \n170: ### Alternative 1: dataclasses instead of Pydantic\n171: \n172: **Approach**: Use Python `dataclasses` for `AgentMetadata` with manual validation methods.\n173: \n174: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n175: |--------|------------|\n176: | Pros | No external dependency; simpler for basic data structures |\n177: | Cons | No automatic validation; more boilerplate; no serialization helpers; no type coercion |\n178: \n179: **Decision**: Rejected. Pydantic provides automatic validation, type coercion, and `model_dump()` for serialization without boilerplate.\n180: \n181: ### Alternative 2: JSON-based metadata storage\n182: \n183: **Approach**: Store metadata as JSON instead of YAML.\n184: \n185: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n186: |--------|------------|\n187: | Pros | Native Python `json` module; no pyyaml dependency; easier machine parsing |\n188: | Cons | Less human-readable; no comments support; spec explicitly requires YAML |\n189: \n190: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires YAML format (`agent_metadata.yaml`) for human-readable configuration with comments.\n191: \n192: ### Alternative 3: Single metadata file in home directory\n193: \n194: **Approach**: Store all agent metadata in a central file (e.g., `~/.agentcube/metadata.yaml`) instead of workspace-local files.\n195: \n196: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n197: |--------|------------|\n198: | Pros | Centralized management; easier multi-agent overview |\n199: | Cons | Workspace independence lost; harder to version control; spec requires per-workspace file |\n200: \n201: **Decision**: Rejected. Spec requires `{workspace}/agent_metadata.yaml` for workspace-local configuration and Git version control.\n202: \n203: ### Alternative 4: Configuration file inheritance/templating\n204: \n205: **Approach**: Support base metadata file with inheritance (e.g., `extends: base-metadata.yaml`).\n206: \n207: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n208: |--------|------------|\n209: | Pros | Reuse common settings; reduce duplication |\n210: | Cons | Adds complexity; not in spec; inheritance resolution overhead |\n211: \n212: **Decision**: Rejected for initial scope. May add as enhancement if users request configuration reuse patterns.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 5. Risks\n217: \n218: | Risk | Mitigation |\n219: |------|------------|\n220: | Invalid YAML syntax | `yaml.safe_load` raises `YAMLDecodeError`; catch and re-raise with context |\n221: | Missing required fields | Pydantic `ValidationError` with field-specific messages |\n222: | Unknown fields in YAML | Pydantic `extra=\"ignore\"` (or forbid per spec requirement) |\n223: | Workspace validation race condition | Check file existence before validation; handle `FileNotFoundError` |\n224: | Language mismatch | `_validate_python_workspace` / `_validate_java_workspace` with clear error messages |\n225: | Port range violation | Pydantic validator `validate_port` raises `ValueError` with valid range |\n226: \n227: ---\n228: \n229: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n230: \n231: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/__init__.py` package marker\n232: - [ ] Create `agentcube/models/pack_models.py` with `MetadataOptions` dataclass\n233: - [ ] Implement `MetadataOptions.from_options(options: Dict[str, Any])` factory method\n234: - [ ] Create `agentcube/services/metadata_service.py` with `MetadataService` class\n235: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.__init__(verbose: bool = False)`\n236: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.load_metadata(workspace_path)` with fallback filenames\n237: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.save_metadata(workspace_path, metadata)` with YAML options\n238: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.update_metadata(workspace_path, updates)` partial update\n239: - [ ] Implement `MetadataService.validate_workspace(workspace_path)` structure check\n240: - [ ] Implement `_validate_python_workspace` for *.py file check\n241: - [ ] Implement `_validate_java_workspace` for pom.xml check\n242: - [ ] Define `AgentMetadata` Pydantic model with all fields\n243: - [ ] Implement `validate_language` validator (python/java lowercase)\n244: - [ ] Implement `validate_build_mode` validator (local/cloud lowercase)\n245: - [ ] Implement `validate_port` validator (1-65535 range)\n246: - [ ] Update `agentcube/services/__init__.py` exports\n247: - [ ] Update `PackRuntime` to use `MetadataService`\n248: - [ ] Add unit tests for metadata load/save with valid YAML\n249: - [ ] Add unit tests for fallback filename behavior\n250: - [ ] Add unit tests for Pydantic validators\n251: - [ ] Add unit tests for workspace validation scenarios\n252: - [ ] Run `pytest tests/test_metadata_service.py` to validate\n253: \n254: ---\n255: \n256: ## 7. References\n257: \n258: - Spec: `cli-toolkit/spec.md` — Requirement: Metadata file format, Workspace validation\n259: - Design: `cli-toolkit/design.md` — MetadataService, AgentMetadata, MetadataOptions signatures\n260: - AR-021 — CLI pack command (uses MetadataService for pack flow)\n261: - AR-022 — CLI publish command (uses metadata for deployment info)\n262: - Pydantic Documentation: https://docs.pydantic.dev/\n263: - PyYAML Documentation: https://pyyaml.org/wiki/PyYAMLDocumentation\n\n(End of file - total 263 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-025 — MetadataService 与数据模型\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-025 |\n| Module | cmd/cli |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nImplement the `MetadataService` and Pydantic data models (`AgentMetadata`, `MetadataOptions`) that form the core configuration layer of AgentCube CLI. These components provide structured YAML-based metadata management for agent lifecycle operations (pack, build, publish, invoke, status), enabling:\n\n1. **Metadata Persistence**: Load/save agent configuration as YAML with fallback file names\n2. **Schema Validation**: Enforce field constraints via Pydantic validators (language, build_mode, port)\n3. **Workspace Validation**: Verify workspace structure based on language (Python *.py, Java pom.xml)","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-025/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775876643193,"end":1775876643201}}}}
